Task: Convert the Corefinity Control Panel into a fully functional, state-driven React SaaS application. Every tab must be interactive.
​1. Environments Command Center (Logic & Data):
​Pods & Nodes Tabs: Create a realistic monitoring dashboard. Use a useEffect to simulate live data—CPU and Memory percentages should fluctuate slightly every few seconds. Use pulsing green dots for "Healthy" statuses.
​Firewall Tab: Implement a working "Add IP" feature. Users can type an IP; clicking "Add" inserts it into a list. Validate for IPv4/IPv6. Include a "Delete" icon for each row.
​Deployments Tab (The Contest Winner): >     * Implement the Sequential Lock: Pipeline > Provider > Repository > Branch.
​If Provider is selected, show a "Checking for accounts..." loader, then show the "No account connected" error if no data exists.
​Deployment Tasks: Show a vertical timeline. The top task should have a "Progress Bar" that actually fills up to 100% to simulate a real deployment.
​2. Support Ticket System (Staff vs. Client UI):
​Ticket View: Build a fully functional chat interface.
​The "Yellow Box" Logic: Create a toggle for "Internal Note" vs. "Public Reply."
​Internal: Background becomes light yellow (#FFFBEB), border becomes gold, and a "Staff Only" badge appears.
​Public: Standard brand styling.
​History Tab: Implement a list of "System Events" (e.g., "Status changed to Pending by Catherine") separate from the chat.
​3. User Profile & Security:
​2FA Setup: Create a functional "Toggle" for Google Authenticator. When turned on, show a mock QR Code and a verification code input field.
​SSH Keys: Allow users to "Add New Key." When saved, it should appear in a list with the date added and a "Remove" button.
​4. Global UX & Polish:
​Navigation: Ensure the "Currently viewing as" dropdown in the top bar works to filter the context.
​Loading States: Add "Skeleton Loaders" for all tables so the UI feels fast and "app-like."
​Orange Links: Ensure every single ID, Environment name, and Company name is an OrangeLink.
​5. Data Persistence (Mock): Use localStorage to save things like added IP addresses or SSH keys so that if the hirer refreshes the page, their data is still there.
